[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### Security Analysis                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m | Aspect | Implementation | Security Level |                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m |---|---|---|                                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m | **Confidentiality** | Base64 only (not encrypted) | **LOW** |              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m | **Integrity** | HMAC-SHA1 with SECRET_KEY | **HIGH** |                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m | **Authenticity** | HMAC-SHA1 signature proves origin | **HIGH** |          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m | **Replay Protection** | Timestamp ensures freshness | **MEDIUM** |         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m | **Protection Dependency** | Entirely on SECRET_KEY secrecy | **CRITICAL**  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m |                                                                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Critical Vulnerability:**                                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - ⚠️ If `SECRET_KEY` is leaked or cracked → **Full session compromise**       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - ⚠️ Can forge any session cookie for any user                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - ⚠️ Flask session cookies are NOT encrypted (readable by client)             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Attack Vectors:**                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. **Secret Key Leakage** (most common): Weak secret in source code,         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m environment variable, config files                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. **Hash Length Extension**: HMAC-SHA1 is secure against this               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. **Brute Force**: If SECRET_KEY is weak (<128 bits)                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 4. **Timing Attacks**: Constant-time comparison mitigates this               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ---                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### Key Takeaways                                                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. ✅ **Flask uses itsdangerous library** for session cookies                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. ✅ **Payload is readable (base64, NOT encrypted)** - visible client-side  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. ✅ **Signature is HMAC-SHA1** with server's SECRET_KEY                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 4. ✅ **Without SECRET_KEY: Can ONLY decode, CANNOT modify or forge**        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 5. ✅ **SECRET_KEY is CRITICAL** - leak = complete session compromise        [32m│[0m
